<br>
    Rods serve to speed up the buffing process before a raid begins, and in long encounters allows the clerics to never be oom.<br>
<br>
    I honestly don't give a hoot about magician nuking power, but I care about pet power, and giving mana to the classes that need it the most.  An epic wizard can do more with the 440 mana I can give him than I can accomplish with the 180 mana I spent to give it to him.  I am not a backup healer, but I can help keep the primary healers from running out of mana.  I'm not a tank, but my pet can do some mana-free melee damage to help the tanks live just a little longer, or the mob a little shorter.<br>
<br>
    Rods are self balanced solo, though.  Nice to have, but not a huge boost to soloing ability.<br>
