Rhasin, you should try an uber of battle of 10-20 minutes someday, if you ever get the chance to. In these scenarios I have 2 options.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Bring more spellcasters to Luclin. They're not as harsh on resistances as they are AC, so overall, your casters will be doing the brunt of the damage while the melee hold aggro. Unless, I missed my interpretation of Luclin mobs in my journeys?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Different guilds fight different things.  When I bring up the debate I'm talking generally, and although it's good to know how much people fight which mobs, I'm still assuming 10% old world, 20% kunark, 30% velious and 50% luclin.   This is assuming more than 1 group = raid and generally for all 50+ guilds in EQ.<br>
<br>
That said no you can't  just bring a bunch of wizards to a raid and nuke the crap out of luclin mobs.  They just have way too much HP.  You can mana dump for about one minute which still leaves 5 more until you get mana back.  And sitting down during this time isn't often smart (specially after mana dumping.)  Which means Tukodo was right, in most luclin encounters, mod rodding is preforable.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
I love rods, and don't consider it overpowering. &lt;snip&gt; I honestly don't give a hoot about magician nuking power, but I care about pet power, and giving mana to the classes that need it the most. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I get lots of comments like this.  Yes I really like mod rods as well, and most mages it seems want more pet power as opposed to nuking power.  Giving to classes that use mana a lot is good.  When you conisign your mana bar for someone else to use thats somewhat a slap in the face unless it's a special circumstance.   Raids aren't special circumstances.  I think this next quote summed my position up best.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
I think the problem most are inderectly refering to is that having such a powerful utility spell puts magicians well ahead of Necromancers and Wizards in raid utility. Even if it doesnt get nerfed, so isnt it likely that magicians will get any raid damage uppgrades compared to those two classes. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This is exactly what I'm driving at.  Mod rod 2 is really good, and I mean reeeeeally good in raids.  It's a strong utility we bring to raids and I'm happy for that, but it's not in the direction which we want to go.   What I fear happening is Verant looking at all our class abilities and not giving us a good per or damage solution to raids in leiu of how useful mod rods already are.<br>
<br>
Someone asked about useful summons.  I agree. We should get some more.  Or rather augment some of the existing ones so they are more useful.  Giving one class breaking skill that is super useful doesn't fix everything else.  Our weapon summon upgrades should be stronger, and bane weapons is an excellent idea.  Including more good missle weapons, or even poison for rogues.  The rest of our summons aren't really useless at all.  Lev rings are still one of the best means for no component levitate, waterstones are superior to EB, coldstones rock over UV spells.  The summons are pretty good.  And make them too much better and we will be a pure support class.<br>
<br>
Finally..<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Manaburn is powerful ,Direcharm is powerful ,/dis Defensive is powerful ,/dis Trueshot is powerful ,Complete Heal is powerful ,Duelist + Backstab is powerful. Isnt it about time mages had something to add to this list? <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Manaburn does a whole bunch of DD damage to a mob, wizards specialize in DD damage.<br>
<br>
Direcharm is another barrel of monkeys, but better things could have been invented for it as well.<br>
<br>
Defense is all about what warriors do best.  Tank.<br>
<br>
Trueshot exemplifies ranger archery which is very class specfic thing for them. (No one can shoot a bow nearly as well as a ranger.)<br>
<br>
Complete heal all about clerics and what they do best.<br>
<br>
Backstab is a huge &quot;rogue thing&quot; to do.<br>
<br>
Summoning mod rods is summoning.. But it's an indirect way to get to something we don't really do.  It's like giving rogues a rare poison that procs ice comet, or monks the ability to summon &quot;monk&quot; skeletal pets.<br>
<br>
What are mages known for?  Summoning yes, but summoning uber pets.  If you are looking for an uber summoning item for mages it turns us to utility.  Which isn't the direction we'd been working for all this time.  And even if you are ok with that it has to be an ability that doesn't impede on another classes ability.  That can be hard to do and still make it uber.<br>
